# ü§ñ AI SRE for Kubernetes (Minikube + Ollama)

This project demonstrates an **AI-powered Site Reliability Engineer (SRE)**
that automatically diagnoses and proposes fixes for common Kubernetes pod failures
using **Ollama (LLM)**.

---

## üß∞ Environment
- OS: Ubuntu 24.04 LTS
- Kubernetes: Minikube
- Container Runtime: Docker
- AI Model: Ollama (Gemma 2B)
- Language: Python 3

---

## 1Ô∏è‚É£ System Update
```bash
sudo apt update -y
sudo apt upgrade -y
2Ô∏è‚É£ Install Required Packages
bash
Copy code
sudo apt install -y curl wget apt-transport-https ca-certificates gnupg lsb-release
3Ô∏è‚É£ Install Docker
bash
Copy code
sudo apt install -y docker.io
sudo systemctl enable docker
sudo systemctl start docker
Allow Docker Without sudo
bash
Copy code
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER
sudo chmod 666 /var/run/docker.sock
newgrp docker
Verify:

bash
Copy code
docker version
4Ô∏è‚É£ Check Virtualization Support
bash
Copy code
egrep -q 'vmx|svm' /proc/cpuinfo && echo yes || echo no
5Ô∏è‚É£ Install Minikube
bash
Copy code
curl -LO https://storage.googleapis.com/minikube/releases/latest/minikube-linux-amd64
sudo install minikube-linux-amd64 /usr/local/bin/minikube
Verify:

bash
Copy code
minikube version
6Ô∏è‚É£ Install kubectl
bash
Copy code
curl -LO "https://dl.k8s.io/release/$(curl -L -s https://dl.k8s.io/release/stable.txt)/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl"
chmod +x kubectl
sudo mv kubectl /usr/local/bin/
Verify:

bash
Copy code
kubectl version --client
7Ô∏è‚É£ Start Minikube (Docker Driver)
bash
Copy code
